{
  "stem": "27507.11",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "After the war, immediately, there was so much chaos that you didn't need any permission.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You could leave Poland somehow without any permission.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The borders were not formally fixed and so on, so people did leave.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then I think in '46 it was still possible to leave, and then it was not possible to leave for some time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then it was possible to leave, I think, for people of-- young men of army age for Israel during the Independence War in Israel in '48, and then again in 1950 when we left.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, there were lots of Jews who went to Israel in 1950.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know how many numbers, but--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh no, we went-- there were trainloads.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were trainloads and boatloads and there must have been altogether thousands, but how many thousands, I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we went to quite officially, except that we had to give up our Polish nationality and give up most of our sayings and give up the furniture which we had.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had practically to go with few belongings, but we weren't quite officially with the train from Warsaw in early-- late January, '50 to Venice.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then in Venice we went on a boat, [ITALIAN], an Italian boat, and we went to Haifa.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we came to Haifa, so there was snow all over in Haifa.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, in February, 1950, there was a lot of snow, strangely enough.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my parents, we all went to start to [INAUDIBLE] camp, which was not a very nice place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we stayed there-- my parents stayed for a bit longer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I stayed only very briefly because I went to my aunt in Tel Aviv, the aunt who came from Warsaw in 1940.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
